description._content: Description: Dar-i-Khazinah. The Pump House from which the entire water supply for the Oil-Fields was drawn before the completion of the Godar Landor station. Location: Dar-i-Khazinah, Persia Description: Dar-i-Khazinah. Interiot of Water Pump House,Tandem Triple Expansion Worthington Pumps in the foreground. Location: Dar-i-Khazinah, Persia Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/714 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives.
